title: "The Substance"
rating: 8.5
review {
  direction {
    director {
      name: "Coralie Fargeat"
    }
    rating: "Very Good"
    comments: "The direction on a macroscale is great as it created a unique vibe that matches the hyper-pop glamour of Hollywood; The direction on a microscale is over-the-top to execute the points they were trying to get across about beauty standards and Hollywood; The storytelling is very good as they use their unique vibe to tell the story; They build tension in a way that is pretty traditional to body horror"
  }
