    }
    cast {
      rating: "Pretty Bad"
      comments: "I understand that all the performances were over-the-top and toneless on purpose because it is supposed to exaggerate Hollywood; but at some point it just becomes bad acting"
    }
    rating: "Pretty Good"
  }
  story {
    writer {
      name: "Coralie Fargeat"
    }
    rating: "Very Good"
    comments: "The concept is very original, as it is a glamorous look at female beauty standards in Hollywood; The plot structure is pretty good, for the most part, as it is very structured, but the movie kind of falls apart toward the final 30 minutes; The character writing is very good, as both leads represent the beauty standards of Hollywood and ageism for women"
  }
  screenplay {
    writer {
      name: "Coralie Fargeat"
    }
    rating: "Good"
    comments: "The dialogue is pretty exaggerated and satirically over-the-top, but this helps complement the vibe; The humor is very satirically over-the-top, that it is kinda funny how dumb it is; The symbolism is the whole point of this movie, as it is an allegory for beauty standards in Hollywood and ageism for women; The foreshadowing is fine, but you can kinda predict where this movie is going by what is happening"
  }
